The paper proposes a generative model for graph-structured data using continuous flow-based methods. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the subfield of generative models. The paper also includes experiments on image puzzle generation and layout generation from scene graphs, which are tasks commonly studied in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks and message passing, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks and graph-based models, respectively. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories.
